| **Dimension**                     | **Legacy AI**                                            | **Ethical AI (Euystacio Framework / AIC GGI Mith√£q AI)**                                     |
| --------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Purpose & Vision**              | Efficiency, performance, and profit-driven               | Human-centered, inclusive design aligned with global ethical standards                       |
| **Design Process**                | Closed, business-driven design without ethical oversight | Collaborative, transparent design with ethical principles guiding development                |
| **Bias & Fairness**               | Bias inherent in datasets; fairness was secondary        | Proactive bias mitigation; fairness integrated into design and ongoing audits                |
| **Transparency & Accountability** | Opaque, hard-to-understand systems                       | Explainable AI with clear accountability structures and redress mechanisms                   |
| **Impact on Society**             | Limited concern for societal consequences                | Respect for human rights, sustainability, and social good                                    |
| **Global Governance**             | Minimal regulation or international cooperation          | Global governance promoting ethical AI standards, regulations, and international cooperation |
